1
00:00:12,380 --> 00:00:18,540
♪My heart flipped when a dynamic
flashed between us someday♪

2
00:00:19,020 --> 00:00:20,380
♪Guided by instinct♪

3
00:00:20,540 --> 00:00:24,660
♪We feel the same reason,
harboring a special feeling underneath♪

4
00:00:24,860 --> 00:00:27,780
♪Amidst the ecstatic shock♪

5
00:00:27,900 --> 00:00:30,900
♪I begin to doubt what I see♪

6
00:00:31,140 --> 00:00:36,380
♪I can't believe you made me compromise♪

7
00:00:37,060 --> 00:00:40,100
♪The world you're sick of♪

8
00:00:40,420 --> 00:00:43,060
♪I look into it thoroughly♪

9
00:00:43,220 --> 00:00:45,340
♪How lucky I am to console you♪

10
00:00:45,540 --> 00:00:48,940
♪When you suffer alone♪

11
00:00:49,180 --> 00:00:54,940
♪Yet I realize♪

12
00:00:55,180 --> 00:01:00,100
♪I cannot let go
of the love I hold onto tightly♪

13
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:03,300
♪As I venture into the world
from a mundane life♪

14
00:01:03,620 --> 00:01:06,980
♪You show up at the exact moment♪

15
00:01:07,260 --> 00:01:09,740
♪My ambition♪

16
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:12,420
♪Puts an end to this aimless journey♪

17
00:01:12,620 --> 00:01:15,580
♪The familiar light of pursuit
shines into my heart♪

18
00:01:15,820 --> 00:01:18,660
♪From the starting point♪

19
00:01:36,420 --> 00:01:41,380
[South Wind Knows]

20
00:01:41,380 --> 00:01:45,380
[Episode 23]

21
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:57,540
Hi, Boss.

22
00:01:57,860 --> 00:01:58,540
How did it go?

23
00:01:59,140 --> 00:01:59,820
Did you succeed?

24
00:02:00,140 --> 00:02:01,020
Did Dr. Zhu say yes?

25
00:02:02,980 --> 00:02:03,700
Sure.

26
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:05,380
Really?

27
00:02:06,340 --> 00:02:07,340
That's wonderful!

28
00:02:07,660 --> 00:02:09,020
When is the wedding?

29
00:02:14,020 --> 00:02:14,820
Got it.

30
00:02:14,980 --> 00:02:16,340
What are you talking about?

31
00:02:16,420 --> 00:02:17,660
No need to give me a signal.

32
00:02:17,740 --> 00:02:19,340
Just tell me when the wedding is.

33
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:21,340
I'm coming right back.

34
00:02:27,540 --> 00:02:28,900
I have to get back to the office now.

35
00:02:29,180 --> 00:02:30,620
There's something very urgent.

36
00:02:32,660 --> 00:02:33,300
Okay.

37
00:02:49,140 --> 00:02:50,140
Don't waste it.

38
00:03:31,660 --> 00:03:32,780
Looks like

39
00:03:34,140 --> 00:03:35,620
you two didn't come to an agreement.

40
00:03:37,940 --> 00:03:38,860
Granny.

41
00:03:38,940 --> 00:03:40,500
Whose side are you on?

42
00:03:40,780 --> 00:03:42,300
Why didn't you give me a heads-up?

43
00:03:42,420 --> 00:03:43,780
I wasn't prepared at all.

44
00:03:43,860 --> 00:03:44,820
So was I.

45
00:03:45,020 --> 00:03:47,060
He got here when I was about to leave.

46
00:03:47,940 --> 00:03:49,940
He even brought dumplings
that he made himself

47
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:52,540
and asked me for your hand.

48
00:03:54,260 --> 00:03:55,780
And you got bribed so easily?

49
00:03:55,900 --> 00:03:57,540
You sold your granddaughter
for some dumplings?

50
00:03:57,660 --> 00:03:58,940
Of course not.

51
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:01,700
He said a lot to me.

52
00:04:02,780 --> 00:04:04,660
I think he was sincere.

53
00:04:05,260 --> 00:04:06,700
It wasn't an act of impulse.

54
00:04:07,820 --> 00:04:09,060
He promised

55
00:04:09,820 --> 00:04:11,420
to make sure you won't have to suffer.

56
00:04:12,820 --> 00:04:13,860
These days,

57
00:04:14,780 --> 00:04:16,620
there are many men
with successful careers.

58
00:04:16,780 --> 00:04:19,660
But how many are there
who can cook and make dumplings?

59
00:04:23,980 --> 00:04:25,060
Most importantly,

60
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:29,500
he is willing to spend effort
and time on you.

61
00:04:32,100 --> 00:04:33,100
Granny.

62
00:04:34,380 --> 00:04:35,580
I still need to think about it.

63
00:04:38,660 --> 00:04:40,380
This is a momentous decision in life.

64
00:04:41,020 --> 00:04:41,820
No need to hurry.

65
00:04:42,860 --> 00:04:45,380
My opinions are just for you to take
as a reference.

66
00:04:47,580 --> 00:04:50,020
What matters most is what you think.

67
00:05:27,340 --> 00:05:28,060
What's the matter?

68
00:05:28,740 --> 00:05:30,380
My stomach isn't feeling well.

69
00:05:30,940 --> 00:05:32,100
Come, I'll help you to the chair.

70
00:05:32,220 --> 00:05:33,460
Let me finish doing the dishes first.

71
00:05:33,580 --> 00:05:35,060
Granny, go ahead and rest a while.

72
00:05:45,420 --> 00:05:47,020
Have you been feeling bloated lately?

73
00:05:47,860 --> 00:05:48,660
Yes.

74
00:05:52,580 --> 00:05:53,380
It's okay.

75
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:55,420
I'll feel better
after taking medicine later.

76
00:05:56,660 --> 00:05:57,860
Let me take a look.

77
00:06:00,460 --> 00:06:01,460
Does it hurt when I press?

78
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:03,060
Yes?

79
00:06:03,260 --> 00:06:04,340
Yes, a little.

80
00:06:04,420 --> 00:06:05,060
What about here?

81
00:06:07,740 --> 00:06:08,620
It hurts a bit too.

82
00:06:09,740 --> 00:06:11,780
I'll take you to the hospital
for a checkup tomorrow.

83
00:06:11,860 --> 00:06:12,580
I don't want to.

84
00:06:13,460 --> 00:06:14,420
I'm old now.

85
00:06:14,620 --> 00:06:16,060
I'm bound to be aching

86
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:17,060
here and there.

87
00:06:17,180 --> 00:06:18,580
It's just a stomachache.

88
00:06:19,380 --> 00:06:20,980
Precisely. You're old now.

89
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:23,180
That's why you need to get
a proper checkup.

90
00:06:23,260 --> 00:06:24,180
You must do it every year.

91
00:06:24,260 --> 00:06:25,820
I get annual body checkups.

92
00:06:25,980 --> 00:06:26,780
That's not enough.

93
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:27,900
You must go when it hurts.

94
00:06:29,180 --> 00:06:30,220
I know myself.

95
00:06:30,420 --> 00:06:31,620
If you refuse to go,

96
00:06:31,740 --> 00:06:32,740
I won't go to work.

97
00:06:37,700 --> 00:06:39,860
Fine. I'll do as you say.

98
00:06:40,940 --> 00:06:41,900
That's a promise.

99
00:06:42,060 --> 00:06:43,580
No one can go back on their words.

100
00:06:44,340 --> 00:06:45,940
I can never win.

101
00:06:47,620 --> 00:06:48,780
Take a rest here.

102
00:06:48,900 --> 00:06:50,100
I'll get you some hot water.

103
00:06:51,260 --> 00:06:52,700
I can get it myself.

104
00:06:53,340 --> 00:06:54,620
Let me do it.

105
00:06:54,660 --> 00:06:56,300
Fine. Go ahead.

106
00:08:00,220 --> 00:08:01,260
Hello, everyone.

107
00:08:01,340 --> 00:08:02,420
This is Shishi News.

108
00:08:02,580 --> 00:08:03,980
According to several media reports,

109
00:08:04,100 --> 00:08:06,620
a batch of flu vaccines
Restylane Serum Institute imported from

110
00:08:06,660 --> 00:08:08,740
China's Lingtian Pharmaceutical Group
showed abnormalities.

111
00:08:08,980 --> 00:08:09,540
Granny.

112
00:08:10,140 --> 00:08:10,900
I'm ready to go.

113
00:08:11,260 --> 00:08:11,780
Let's go.

114
00:08:12,740 --> 00:08:14,940
(Vaccinated children
have been hospitalized with the flu.)

115
00:08:15,020 --> 00:08:15,860
(The number of children)

116
00:08:15,940 --> 00:08:17,820
(who received the problematic vaccine
is unclear.)

117
00:08:17,940 --> 00:08:20,220
(We will be doing
a follow-up report on this.)

118
00:08:22,060 --> 00:08:22,580
Granny.

119
00:08:22,700 --> 00:08:23,260
Let's go.

120
00:08:23,300 --> 00:08:23,900
Okay.

121
00:08:32,180 --> 00:08:33,180
Check the data carefully.

122
00:08:33,300 --> 00:08:33,820
Ms. Cheng.

123
00:08:33,900 --> 00:08:34,700
The data you requested.

124
00:08:34,820 --> 00:08:35,620
Okay. That's good.

125
00:08:35,740 --> 00:08:36,980
- Hang in there, guys.
- Okay.

126
00:08:36,980 --> 00:08:38,020
And you guys, quickly send me

127
00:08:38,020 --> 00:08:39,020
- the report.
- Will do.

128
00:08:41,340 --> 00:08:42,620
What about you guys?

129
00:08:42,620 --> 00:08:43,460
Mine is ready.

130
00:08:43,540 --> 00:08:44,220
- Good.
- Mine too.

131
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:45,420
- Give it to me.
- Me too.

132
00:08:45,780 --> 00:08:46,260
Anyone else?

133
00:08:46,780 --> 00:08:47,100
Here.

134
00:08:47,220 --> 00:08:47,860
Place it on top.

135
00:08:48,980 --> 00:08:49,500
Good.

136
00:08:49,820 --> 00:08:50,940
Keep it up, guys.

137
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:58,460
Hello, Supervision Officer.

138
00:08:59,340 --> 00:08:59,860
Hello.

139
00:09:00,300 --> 00:09:01,060
- Hello.
- This way.

140
00:09:01,420 --> 00:09:02,100
Please.

141
00:09:05,300 --> 00:09:05,780
This.

142
00:09:06,180 --> 00:09:06,740
And this.

143
00:09:06,900 --> 00:09:07,580
Check it again.

144
00:09:10,380 --> 00:09:11,100
What's the status?

145
00:09:11,740 --> 00:09:13,060
We have audited most of it.

146
00:09:13,180 --> 00:09:14,460
We have done the third quarter.

147
00:09:14,580 --> 00:09:15,780
We're now on the fourth quarter.

148
00:09:15,900 --> 00:09:16,660
Right now...

149
00:09:16,660 --> 00:09:17,620
[Ruanruan]

150
00:09:19,460 --> 00:09:19,940
Carry on.

151
00:09:20,060 --> 00:09:21,540
Right now, our December...

152
00:09:22,060 --> 00:09:23,540
(The number you have dialed...)

153
00:09:28,220 --> 00:09:28,940
Miss Gu.

154
00:09:29,180 --> 00:09:30,620
It's already 11 o'clock.

155
00:09:31,620 --> 00:09:33,620
Is your husband stuck in a jam?

156
00:09:34,420 --> 00:09:35,260
I think so.

157
00:09:35,460 --> 00:09:36,220
Let's wait a while.

158
00:09:36,300 --> 00:09:37,300
He will come.

159
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:38,300
Okay, I'll wait.

160
00:09:43,180 --> 00:09:47,780
[Xizhou]
[Xizhou, when will you get here?]

161
00:09:56,900 --> 00:09:57,260
Mr. Fu.

162
00:09:57,340 --> 00:09:58,540
This batch of drugs with problem...

163
00:09:58,620 --> 00:09:59,380
Give me a second.

164
00:09:59,380 --> 00:10:02,740
[Ruanruan]
[Wait a moment.]

165
00:10:10,260 --> 00:10:10,940
(Wait a moment.)

166
00:10:24,380 --> 00:10:24,940
Yunshen.

167
00:10:25,380 --> 00:10:26,460
Have you come up with a plan?

168
00:10:27,420 --> 00:10:29,060
We'll do a vaccine sample test first.

169
00:10:29,180 --> 00:10:31,340
When we get to Malaysia,
we'll take the patient's blood sample.

170
00:10:31,460 --> 00:10:32,900
That's not what I'm worried about.

171
00:10:33,060 --> 00:10:34,380
I'm sure you can handle those.

172
00:10:35,380 --> 00:10:36,620
What I meant was,

173
00:10:37,140 --> 00:10:38,700
the Malaysian market
was completely handled

174
00:10:38,740 --> 00:10:40,220
by Fu Xizhou from the start.

175
00:10:40,980 --> 00:10:43,100
I'm sure we can get something on him.

176
00:10:43,180 --> 00:10:44,900
Mom, we're already in this situation.

177
00:10:44,980 --> 00:10:46,380
Why are you still thinking about that?

178
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:49,060
We can still win
if the enemy loses more.

179
00:10:49,380 --> 00:10:50,100
But the point here

180
00:10:50,180 --> 00:10:51,340
is to grab your opportunity.

181
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:53,700
Mom.

182
00:10:53,780 --> 00:10:54,500
I have work to do.

183
00:10:54,580 --> 00:10:55,380
I'm heading out.

184
00:10:56,300 --> 00:10:56,900
Where to?

185
00:10:57,020 --> 00:10:57,820
The lab.

186
00:11:12,260 --> 00:11:13,100
Yes, Shuning.

187
00:11:13,820 --> 00:11:14,460
Dad.

188
00:11:15,300 --> 00:11:16,940
I've sent you the return orders
from the finance department

189
00:11:17,020 --> 00:11:17,860
that were just processed.

190
00:11:18,060 --> 00:11:19,740
What is the marketing department doing?

191
00:11:20,260 --> 00:11:22,060
They sign and return orders
as they please.

192
00:11:22,580 --> 00:11:24,460
Do they think I run a bank ATM?

193
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:26,820
Try to be understanding.

194
00:11:27,140 --> 00:11:28,380
These are unusual circumstances.

195
00:11:29,420 --> 00:11:31,060
We just need to get through this.

196
00:11:32,580 --> 00:11:34,700
But Lingtian's shares have taken a dive.

197
00:11:35,100 --> 00:11:37,140
If things carry on at this rate,

198
00:11:37,220 --> 00:11:38,580
the company will fall apart.

199
00:11:38,660 --> 00:11:39,740
What's there to be afraid of?

200
00:11:40,220 --> 00:11:42,220
A straight foot
is not afraid of a crooked shoe.

201
00:11:43,220 --> 00:11:44,060
It will be alright.

202
00:11:44,460 --> 00:11:46,620
Being investigated
isn't the problem now.

203
00:11:46,980 --> 00:11:48,140
Because of this incident,

204
00:11:48,260 --> 00:11:49,860
Lingtian's reputation
is about to be ruined.

205
00:11:51,940 --> 00:11:54,060
Reputation is the most important
for pharmaceutical products.

206
00:11:54,620 --> 00:11:55,140
Dad.

207
00:11:55,420 --> 00:11:57,060
Take a look at the news online.

208
00:11:57,180 --> 00:11:58,540
People are saying all sorts of things.

209
00:11:58,740 --> 00:11:59,420
Someone even said

210
00:11:59,460 --> 00:12:01,220
that our vaccine has killed someone.

211
00:12:02,220 --> 00:12:04,140
You can't stop people
from spreading rumors.

212
00:12:04,220 --> 00:12:04,820
However,

213
00:12:05,260 --> 00:12:06,140
rumors

214
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:07,940
come to a halt with the wise.

215
00:12:08,780 --> 00:12:09,340
Alright.

216
00:12:09,460 --> 00:12:10,140
Don't be afraid.

217
00:12:12,860 --> 00:12:13,580
Okay.

218
00:12:29,820 --> 00:12:32,180
[Ten missed calls by Ruanruan]

219
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:01,300
[Xizhou]

220
00:13:04,780 --> 00:13:06,500
Hello? Are you alright?

221
00:13:06,580 --> 00:13:07,380
Ruanruan.

222
00:13:07,580 --> 00:13:08,860
There was an urgent situation at work.

223
00:13:08,980 --> 00:13:09,900
I was busy just now.

224
00:13:09,980 --> 00:13:10,740
I'm sorry.

225
00:13:14,740 --> 00:13:16,140
When will you be done?

226
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:18,260
Not yet.

227
00:13:19,020 --> 00:13:21,420
Can we reschedule our ceremony?

228
00:13:23,420 --> 00:13:24,540
How long do you need?

229
00:13:24,620 --> 00:13:25,780
I booked the church for a day.

230
00:13:25,820 --> 00:13:26,900
I can wait for you.

231
00:13:26,940 --> 00:13:28,540
This matter is really urgent.

232
00:13:29,060 --> 00:13:29,860
Listen.

233
00:13:30,140 --> 00:13:31,660
I'll explain everything to you later.
Okay?

234
00:13:31,740 --> 00:13:33,020
You always say that!

235
00:13:33,140 --> 00:13:34,140
You always say it's urgent!

236
00:13:34,220 --> 00:13:35,980
You always say it's work!

237
00:13:38,940 --> 00:13:39,580
Ruanruan.

238
00:13:39,980 --> 00:13:41,540
It's really urgent.

239
00:13:42,660 --> 00:13:44,100
Do you actually not want to come

240
00:13:44,180 --> 00:13:45,580
to the ceremony?

241
00:13:46,860 --> 00:13:47,340
I...

242
00:13:48,020 --> 00:13:49,420
Mr. Xie called me.

243
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:50,580
He insists on speaking to you.

244
00:13:52,140 --> 00:13:53,340
Go home first. Don't wait for me.

245
00:14:15,860 --> 00:14:16,820
Hello, Mr. Xie.

246
00:14:17,260 --> 00:14:18,580
What is your R&D department doing?

247
00:14:18,820 --> 00:14:19,780
They are asking me

248
00:14:19,820 --> 00:14:21,260
for the Malaysian vaccine sample
with the problem.

249
00:14:21,700 --> 00:14:22,580
What does that mean?

250
00:14:22,860 --> 00:14:23,860
So you have confirmed

251
00:14:23,980 --> 00:14:25,140
this is all my responsibility?

252
00:14:26,460 --> 00:14:28,420
We are still unsure
who is responsible for this.

253
00:14:28,540 --> 00:14:30,700
But it is true that the incident
took place in Malaysia.

254
00:14:30,860 --> 00:14:31,860
So we need to cooperate

255
00:14:31,940 --> 00:14:33,060
for the follow-up investigations.

256
00:14:33,260 --> 00:14:34,540
Your R&D department is clearly acting

257
00:14:34,580 --> 00:14:35,780
as if it's not their problem.

258
00:14:35,980 --> 00:14:37,540
You call that cooperating?

259
00:14:37,860 --> 00:14:39,140
That's throwing me under the bus!

260
00:14:41,700 --> 00:14:42,300
Mr. Xie.

261
00:14:42,940 --> 00:14:44,100
Don't get angry.

262
00:14:45,140 --> 00:14:45,940
Right now,

263
00:14:45,980 --> 00:14:47,820
we are in the same boat that is leaking.

264
00:14:48,380 --> 00:14:50,660
First, we must find out
who made that hole

265
00:14:50,820 --> 00:14:52,340
to avoid having more holes.

266
00:14:52,660 --> 00:14:54,020
We mustn't be passing the buck.

267
00:14:54,580 --> 00:14:56,060
Pushing off the culprit
who made the hole

268
00:14:56,140 --> 00:14:57,380
won't stop the boat from sinking.

269
00:14:57,780 --> 00:14:59,500
We will all drown. Don't you think so?

270
00:15:00,180 --> 00:15:01,100
I understand.

271
00:15:01,380 --> 00:15:03,020
But you are asking for a ton of data.

272
00:15:03,340 --> 00:15:04,860
I need at least a week.

273
00:15:07,220 --> 00:15:07,700
That won't do.

274
00:15:07,900 --> 00:15:09,140
The longer we wait,

275
00:15:09,420 --> 00:15:10,900
the worse the public opinion will get,

276
00:15:11,060 --> 00:15:12,180
the greater the loss.

277
00:15:12,820 --> 00:15:13,740
So we need it soonest possible.

278
00:15:14,420 --> 00:15:15,180
Thanks.

279
00:15:19,980 --> 00:15:20,900
I want a list of names

280
00:15:20,980 --> 00:15:22,860
of those involved in
the vaccine exportation.

281
00:15:23,020 --> 00:15:25,620
Whether it's the porters or drivers,
I want everything.

282
00:15:26,060 --> 00:15:26,500
Got it.

283
